This is a prompt blog. Most of these prompts will be by me and they'll be limited to fandoms I know.

Submissions are acceptable so long as they follow the rules, if not I'll just delete them.

summary: Fandom: Game of Thrones Characters: Arya Stark, the Stark Children, Sansa Stark, Jon Snow, Bran Stark, Rickon Stark if you want...
body:
Fandom: Game of Thrones
Characters: Arya Stark, the Stark Children, Sansa Stark, Jon Snow, Bran Stark, Rickon Stark if you want
Warnings: Violence, Character Death(s), War, most things GoT has really

Prompt: The surviving Stark children find their last sister in Braavos but Arya is in the middle of training to be no one and knows the price of abandoning that training for those she loves highest. It’s not one she’s willing to pay, leaving her choices between forcing them to leave without her or ensuring that she won’t be pursued for going with them.

- kunnskat on AO3

title: The Grand Northern Conspiracy
body: It would have been nice for the show to dabble into the Grand Northern Conspiracy theory in a way. Having Sansa as the one who starts the conspiracy and intends to crown Jon as King of the Seven Kingdoms. Well, she kind of did start it off, but we didn’t get a proper pay-off in the Dragonpit scene.

description:
Theon thought he was for death.

And though the last image he would remember was the frozen world tilted on its axis as he lay on his side with his own spear in his abdomen, his last vision was of Sansa Stark’s blue ocean eyes.

He sank into them.

I accidentally fell into the rabbit hole of shipping Theon and Sansa. Sorry in advance. (they’re just so pretty and sad)

❄️🐺❄️

body:
🐺.Sansa Stark of Winterfell.🕊

✨.Little Bird.✨

My skin has turned

to porcelain,

to ivory,

to steel.

❄️🐺❄️

Brave. Sansa took a deep breath.

I am a Stark, yes, I can be brave.

❄️🕊❄️

Is it all lies,

forever and ever,

everyone and everything?
